{"TopicId":152236,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Constant pitch/yaw/roll input?","CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-18T17:48:23Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-18T17:48:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just did something and I don\u0027t know why but one of my rovers keeps the pitch input at the fullest. Is there some sort of key combo that keeps the current input permanently? How do I reset it? I tried Ctrl\u002BW, Ctrol\u002BS, Shift\u002BW, Shift\u002BS, Alt\u002BW and Alt\u002BS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Palaceviking","CreatedById":166883,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-18T17:51:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt-x to cancel trim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027ve added trim by pressing alt-s?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh and do you have any reaction wheels trying to pitch while driving?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"monstah","CreatedById":95210,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-18T17:53:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt\u002BWASDQE controls the trim, which is this permanent input you\u0027ve seen. Hold alt\u002BS on the pad, for example, and watch the control inputs on the bottom left slowly change, then let go and see them stay that way. Alt\u002Bx cancels it, as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/166883-palaceviking/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022166883\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/166883-palaceviking/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Palaceviking\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-18T17:54:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222855517\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152236\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479491467\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Palaceviking\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Palaceviking said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlt-x to cancel trim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027ve added trim by pressing alt-s?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh and do you have any reaction wheels trying to pitch while driving?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a ton. I keep forgetting how to disable it. I don\u0027t remember what I did. Probably held \u0022W\u0022 and phys-warped (with alt). I\u0027ve disabled the wheels fortunately.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jarin","CreatedById":71395,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-19T07:36:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222855524\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152236\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479491692\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002239636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Veeltch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Veeltch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably held \u0022W\u0022 and phys-warped (with alt).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have broken at least half a dozen rovers this way. Especially since trim overrules \u0022\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E Only\u0022 settings on reaction wheels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}